The packaging is the most ridiculous and absurd thing ever. I spent a good half hour of my life trying to get the plastic off of this pencil, and still it isn't all the way off. I tried scissors, teeth, bashing it against the sink in frustration and still the plastic was nearly impossible to get off. The frustration of getting it opened was almost not worth it at all. I actually had to hold a lighter and melt the part of the wrapper off that is near where the caps clicks on, just to be able to twist it off. I may have a mangled, scratched, and slightly melted cap now, but at least I can apply my eye liner.
Like the product however, the bottles  leaked because the cap was open and lost over half of the product. Would like to get one of the packages replaced. It was a slight mess when I received it.

Pertinent info:  My wife is a professional stylist and the following comments hopefully will be useful to potential buyers.  The blower was purchased directly from a professional hair styling supplier and not from Amazon.
The blower has been in almost daily use for 6 months, so the reliability so far is very good.  She likes the heat and air output.  She considers this one of the best blowers she has owned (she tried many blowers over her long career). The only annoying problem is the attachments will not stay on the blower, and without the attachments the performance suffers.  She will buy this model again if the problem with the loose attachment can be resolved.
